				<outline text="Has Twitter ever added a new feature that made you feel like they care about users like you." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 19:09:47 GMT" tweetId="1425534931300667406" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425534931300667406" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="2017: I used to have a better blog. It accommodated and focused my thinking instead of limiting and scattering it. I'm just writing this evening to say I want my old blog back. I liked the freedom. My ideas flowed better. https://t.co/t9O16nXhw4" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 18:45:06 GMT" tweetId="1425528718727028737" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425528718727028737" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="1/4 One of the reasons I prefer to write on the open web rather than on Facebook is that if I get an Aha! idea about a feature, on my blog I can implement it. On Facebook I'm just a user." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:13:09 GMT" tweetId="1425505581364924417" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425505581364924417" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/4 That was/is one of the great things about the web. Anyone can develop features for it. On Facebook, just their employees can. No wonder it never moves." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:13:11 GMT" tweetId="1425505589602529284" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425505589602529284" inReplyToId="1425505581364924417" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="3/4 When a company dominates an activity, they tend to invest elsewhere. Seems kind of perverse, but that's why markets don't always evolve to fill every niche." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:13:12 GMT" tweetId="1425505593800990722" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425505593800990722" inReplyToId="1425505589602529284" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="4/4 Open platforms are more favorable. If you want to perform a new style of music in Central Park, you can. If you want to do it in Carnegie Hall or Lincoln Center, you need to get the approval of a lot of rich people" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:13:14 GMT" tweetId="1425505602059612167" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425505602059612167" inReplyToId="1425505593800990722" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
								<outline text="We gotta get outta here. Twitter too. They never make it better. It's real societal and technologic paralysis." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:34:58 GMT" tweetId="1425511070085664769" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425511070085664769" inReplyToId="1425505602059612167" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="House Democrats can get some of Trump's tax records from accounting firm Mazars USA, judge rules. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnn.com/2021/08/11/politics/trump-taxes-mazars-house-democrats/index.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 16:34:28 GMT" tweetId="1425495845516963843" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425495845516963843" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="1/6 Most of the people my age when we were in school never imagined computers would be used by normal people to communicate. They resisted the idea." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:06:57 GMT" tweetId="1425443621873008642" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443621873008642" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/6 So what are most of us, not just boomers, missing today? I think it has to do with who will be doing our daily journalism. Imho, we all will. Why?" type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:06:58 GMT" tweetId="1425443626147061767" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443626147061767" inReplyToId="1425443621873008642" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="3/6 A void is being left as professional journalists focus on fewer stories." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:06:59 GMT" tweetId="1425443630400016389" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443630400016389" inReplyToId="1425443626147061767" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="4/6 We’re learning how to do it with blogging and social media." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:07:00 GMT" tweetId="1425443634741059585" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443634741059585" inReplyToId="1425443630400016389" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
								<outline text="5/6 We need and want journalism." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:07:02 GMT" tweetId="1425443643029139458" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443643029139458" inReplyToId="1425443634741059585" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
									<outline text="6/6 It’s like jury duty, it’s uplifting, gives our life purpose and meaning. It’s its own reward." type="tweet" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 13:07:03 GMT" tweetId="1425443647340822529" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1425443647340822529" inReplyToId="1425443643029139458" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
