					<outline text="The next breakthrough will not come from Google or any of the other big companies who will cripple the web because they want to protect ad revenue." type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 14:19:21 GMT" tweetId="1421475573218619397" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1421475573218619397" inReplyToId="1421475572216123400" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="It'll come from someone trying out a new idea that only they get. Someone without the time or resources to jump through all of Google's hoops. Someone Google would never hire. Or tolerate if they did accidentally hire them." type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 14:19:21 GMT" tweetId="1421475574103650304" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1421475574103650304" inReplyToId="1421475573218619397" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="What's esp stupid about Brave acting like a big company is that they aren't. Their supposed business model is dependent on the news industry getting risky and entrepreneurial. A very long shot. They need friends. Being a bully -- not a good idea for a startup." type="tweet" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2021 14:19:21 GMT" tweetId="1421475574946611203" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1421475574946611203" inReplyToId="1421475574103650304" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
