				<outline text="1/3 [[Bezos]] wants to move manufacturing into space. I had never heard that idea before seeing a quick interview today with Anderson Cooper of CNN and the two Bezos brothers, who look very much alike. The rich one is the guy in the dorky cowboy hat. He says some industries that" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 20:42:28 GMT" tweetId="1417585722601705486" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1417585722601705486" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/3 use up too much of the earth's resources would be better in space. I started to think about what he might have in mind. Server farms run on solar energy, and cooled by the vacuum of space. Perfect. On the other hand, who would regulate his businesses in space? No OSHA, no" type="tweet" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 20:42:29 GMT" tweetId="1417585726603108352" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1417585726603108352" inReplyToId="1417585722601705486" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
