				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.memeorandum.com/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;  which has been a regular stop for me for news is now mostly links to news behind paywalls. I couldn’t possibly pay for most of them, too many subs to manage, and I don’t read enough of any individual pub to justify subscribing." type="tweet" created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 17:47:03 GMT" tweetId="1416816802517159947" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1416816802517159947" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="I do subscribe to NYT and Washington Post. But I don’t get enough value from either, honestly.

