				<outline text="1/3 Every time I switch my iPhone to a different computer, I have to start over with music. Why. After 15 years or so, couldn't they offer a way to back it up and then restore it? This must be some kind of copyright thing. I wish I had a phone that was rationally designed with" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:36 GMT" tweetId="1413496058047434759" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496058047434759" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/3 the user in mind. I also have an Android phone, but as far as I can tell they broke the only way to copy music onto the device from a Mac. Not sure if a Windows machine is any better. Same reason I'd love to move my desktop act to Linux, but I can't do it without Frontier." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:38 GMT" tweetId="1413496066347986944" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496066347986944" inReplyToId="1413496058047434759" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="3/3 Which is, btw, why I had to buy a new Mac. I mistakenly updated my iPhone and it wouldn't work with the Mac I keep un-updated so I can continue to run Frontier. All I have to say is this: Oy. What a mess." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:39 GMT" tweetId="1413496070403883010" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496070403883010" inReplyToId="1413496066347986944" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="BTW, when I watch people slowly add to threads trying to make it work, I wonder why they don't just use https://t.co/KAVhNd06pG. It's a writing tool designed specifically for Twitter threads. Write it, tweak it up, look at the preview, tweak some more, publish. Boom." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:52:52 GMT" tweetId="1413496377016004609" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496377016004609" inReplyToId="1413496070403883010" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
