				<outline text="Say I want to give someone $10K to keep some of the domains I've registered going for say 100 years. And I give them say 10GB of static content. Add another $10K. https://t.co/iWdYBnbsFk" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 22:43:10 GMT" tweetId="1411093118229921793" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411093118229921793" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="Back to the Future with RSS. &lt;a href=&quot;https://ncase.me/rss/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 22:44:17 GMT" tweetId="1411093399017607176" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411093399017607176" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="1/6 I was glad to see @zittrain write about making the web future-safe. I'd love to work on this with him and others. I don't think the way we're going about it has much of a chance of working." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:27:42 GMT" tweetId="1411074123569287169" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074123569287169" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/6 I think we'll get better results sooner if we go for a sustainable web. That will require new financial structures and organizations that have longevity built into their models, for example, universities like Harvard. Insurance companies." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:27:46 GMT" tweetId="1411074140078067715" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074140078067715" inReplyToId="1411074123569287169" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="3/6 Say I want to give someone $10K to keep some of the domains I've registered going for say 100 years. And I give them say 10GB of static content. Add another $10K." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:27:50 GMT" tweetId="1411074156771356672" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074156771356672" inReplyToId="1411074140078067715" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="4/6 Set up systems to keep the archive of the static content up to date." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:27:54 GMT" tweetId="1411074173649178627" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074173649178627" inReplyToId="1411074156771356672" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
								<outline text="5/6 And let it be cloneable so many vendors can provide this service for a fee, and let app devs create automatic flows on behalf of users." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:27:58 GMT" tweetId="1411074190531252228" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074190531252228" inReplyToId="1411074173649178627" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
									<outline text="6/6 It seems it should be possible from there, if enough people and organizations pay money for longevity, at least it's a start." type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 21:28:02 GMT" tweetId="1411074207199514626" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1411074207199514626" inReplyToId="1411074190531252228" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
									</outline>
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
